<p>I've the below managed bean</p>  <pre><code>@ManagedBean @RequestScoped public class customerBean {      private Customer customer;     private CustomerJpaController customerJpa;      @PostConstruct     public void init() {         customer = new Customer();     }      public String addCustomer() throws Exception {         customerJpa.create(customer);         return "customer";     }      // getter and setter } </code></pre>  <p>The <code>CustomerJpaController</code> looks like below:</p>  <pre><code>public class CustomerJpaController implements Serializable {      @PersistenceContext(unitName = "JFSCustomerPU")     private EntityManagerFactory emf = null;     private UserTransaction utx = null;      public CustomerJpaController(UserTransaction utx, EntityManagerFactory emf) {         this.utx = utx;         this.emf = emf;     }      // ... } </code></pre>  <p>When <code>addCustomer()</code> is invoked from the view, it throws <code>java.lang.NullPointerException</code> at line <code>customerJpa.create(customer);</code>. How is this caused and how can I solve it?</p>